be devastated, too.

02:44.642 --> 02:46.078
You know that, right?
He's going to be totally PO'ed.

02:46.209 --> 02:47.732
- Yeah, but just--okay, you're
not gonna say anything to him,

02:47.863 --> 02:48.777
and I'll tell him
when the time is right.

02:48.907 --> 02:50.561
- Good, good.
When is that gonna be?

02:50.692 --> 02:52.737
On your way
to the fucking airport?

02:52.868 --> 02:54.565
Fuck, Jimmy.

02:54.696 --> 02:55.827
Well, you should
at least tell Mom.

02:55.958 --> 02:57.612
She'll know best
how to break it to him.

02:57.742 --> 03:00.397
- Oh, I've already heard.
- Jesus.

03:00.528 --> 03:01.964
You know,
thanks a lot, Genie.

03:02.094 --> 03:03.139
Thanks.
- Can you believe that he's

03:03.270 --> 03:05.010
gonna be gone the whole
freaking summer?

03:05.141 --> 03:06.011
I mean, Dad is gonna have

03:06.142 --> 03:07.839
a coronary
when he hears this news.

03:07.970 --> 03:10.451
- Which is why you're gonna
tell him James, not me.

03:13.845 --> 03:16.718
- Michael.
Michael.

03:16.848 --> 03:18.763
- What?
- Michael.

03:21.549 --> 03:23.072
Just the man
I was looking for.

03:23.203 --> 03:24.421
Do you know what day it is?

03:24.552 --> 03:25.988
- I don't know.Sunday?

03:26.118 --> 03:28.208
- Today is your
one year anniversary.

03:28.338 --> 03:30.035
Don't you remember?
