03:30.166 --> 03:31.646
you told me you were
gonna piss away

03:31.776 --> 03:33.474
your college education
and do whatever the hell

03:33.604 --> 03:34.779
it is you do out there
in that garage.

03:34.910 --> 03:36.607
- Mom, you know what I do.
Okay, I paint.

03:36.738 --> 03:38.130
Every single day
I'm back there painting.

03:38.261 --> 03:39.828
- Yeah, and you asked
your father and I to give you

03:39.958 --> 03:41.786
one year to pursue
that pipe dream.

03:41.917 --> 03:44.180
But guess what?
Today, that year is up.

03:44.311 --> 03:45.921
So I'm gonna need you
to get your suit pressed

03:46.051 --> 03:46.965
and your shoes shined,

03:47.096 --> 03:48.402
and get your ass into the city

03:48.532 --> 03:50.099
to find a real job.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.449
Or else I'm gonna need you
to find someplace else to live.

03:52.580 --> 03:54.625
- Oh, come on, Mom.Really?

03:54.756 --> 03:56.801
Look, I already told you this,
what, like a thousand times.

03:56.932 --> 03:59.021
I don't want
to be an accountant.

03:59.151 --> 04:01.502
Okay?
I'm gonna be an artist.

04:01.632 --> 04:02.938
- Victor--
- But in the meantime...

04:03.068 --> 04:04.418
- He said it again.
- I just got to figure it out.

04:04.548 --> 04:05.984
Can you please come out here
and talk some sense to him?

04:06.115 --> 04:07.812
Because if he keeps going on
about this artist nonsense,

04:07.943 --> 04:09.118
I'm gonna lose my mind.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.903
[both speaking Spanish]

04:15.777 --> 04:17.300
Remember, we didn't send you
to college to be an artist.

04:17.431 --> 04:21.086
We sent you so you could get
an education and a real job.

04:21.217 --> 04:23.045
- Okay, so--so what do
you want me to do, huh?

04:23.175 --> 04:24.481
You want me to just
give up on my dream?

04:24.612 --> 04:25.830
Is that--is that what you want?

04:25.961 --> 04:28.137
- Yes, exactly.
And you know what else?

04:28.268 --> 04:30.052
Maybe you should come to mass
with your father and I.

04:30.182 --> 04:31.271
Pray for forgiveness

04:31.401 --> 04:32.924
for causing your parents
such heartache.

04:33.055 --> 04:35.884
Pray to Jesus to get you back
on the right path again.

04:36.014 --> 04:38.974
- Mom, Jesus doesn't care
whether or not

04:39.104 --> 04:41.803
I'm a painter or an artist
or an accountant or--

04:41.933 --> 04:43.631
- Maybe he doesn't, but we do.

04:43.761 --> 04:45.894
And we own this house.

04:46.024 --> 04:47.287
- Whatever.

04:49.289 --> 04:52.596
- My head is in fucking pieces.

04:52.727 --> 04:54.816
Ooh, is that tea?

04:54.946 --> 04:56.774
- Oh, we drink tea now?
No.

04:56.905 --> 04:57.862
It's fucking coffee.

04:59.734 --> 05:00.778
Rough night?

05:00.909 --> 05:02.737
- No.
Great night.

05:02.867 --> 05:04.652
Rough morning, thanks to you.

05:06.828 --> 05:08.133
What's this big audition
you got anyhow?

05:08.264 --> 05:11.136
- Oh, it's actually
for an off-Broadway musical.

05:11.267 --> 05:13.182
But it's not just
for the ensemble.

05:13.313 --> 05:16.185
It's for one of the leads,
so it's kind of a big deal,

05:16.316 --> 05:19.667
and that's why I needed
to work on it this morning.

05:19.797 --> 05:21.408
Not that you would care.

05:21.538 --> 05:22.713
- Mm-hmm.

05:22.844 --> 05:24.715
What?

05:24.846 --> 05:25.977
Aw.

05:26.108 --> 05:28.023
Hey, break a leg.

05:28.153 --> 05:30.112
- Yeah, thanks.

05:30.242 --> 05:32.810
Feel better.

05:32.941 --> 05:35.987
- Okay, so this is what
I'm thinking, right.

05:36.118 --> 05:37.946
I don't want to get a real job,
which means my parents

05:38.076 --> 05:39.121
are gonna kick my ass
out of the house,

05:39.251 --> 05:41.123
and I can't afford
a place on my own.

05:41.253 --> 05:44.953
So I was thinking
about asking Tammy

05:45.083 --> 05:46.998
if she wanted
to get a place together.

05:47.129 --> 05:49.000
- I think that
that is a great idea,

05:49.131 --> 05:50.915
as long as she agrees
to join the band.

05:51.046 --> 05:52.787
- Not gonna happen.
That was a one shot deal.

05:52.917 --> 05:54.832
- Can we forget about the band
for one second, okay?

05:54.963 --> 05:57.139
Dude, you realize Tammy would
never go for that, right?

05:57.269 --> 05:58.270
- Why do you say that?

05:58.401 --> 05:59.968
- 'Cause she's
a good Catholic girl.

06:00.098 --> 06:02.013
And living with you would be,
like, living in sin.

06:02.144 --> 06:04.973
Besides, even if she wanted to,
her mother would never have it.

06:05.103 --> 06:07.105
She'd sooner
cut your balls off.

06:07.236 --> 06:08.977
If you wanted to move in with
her, you'd have to marry her.

06:09.107 --> 06:10.761
- You know,
I have been thinking

06:10.892 --> 06:13.590
about the exact same thing.

06:13.721 --> 06:15.418
- Sorry, what?
- No.

06:15.549 --> 06:17.202
- Did you just say--did he just
say what I think he just said?

06:17.333 --> 06:18.508
- He did, he said it.

06:18.639 --> 06:21.076
- [laughing]
Why is that such a crazy idea?

06:21.206 --> 06:22.033
Huh?
I mean, we've been dating

06:22.164 --> 06:24.949
for what, almost a--a year?

06:25.080 --> 06:26.864
I know my mom keeps
asking me about it,

06:26.995 --> 06:28.431
and her mother keeps
asking her about it.

06:28.562 --> 06:29.606
And I know they both keep
seeing each other at church

06:29.737 --> 06:30.955
and asking each other about it.

06:31.086 --> 06:32.783
So I'm, like,
you know what? It's time.

06:32.914 --> 06:34.176
I love her,
I'm making Mama proud

06:34.306 --> 06:36.047
and I'm feeling good,
so why not?

06:36.178 --> 06:39.094
- Well, that's great that
your mothers are discussing it,

06:39.224 --> 06:41.270
but have you actually talked
to Tammy about this?

06:41.401 --> 06:44.012
- Yes, I have, Pags,
actually a bunch of times.

06:44.142 --> 06:45.230
And I know we've said,
you know,

06:45.361 --> 06:47.407
maybe we'd do it after
she gets her MBA and stuff.

06:47.537 --> 06:49.365
But now I'm thinking that
if I ask her to marry me now,

06:49.496 --> 06:51.236
she'll move in with me
if we're engaged.

06:51.367 --> 06:52.760
- Well, I think that's still

06:52.890 --> 06:54.283
classifies as living in sin,
my friend.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.154
- Yeah, I don't think there's
an amendment to the rule.

06:56.285 --> 06:57.895
- I also don't think
that this is the way

06:58.026 --> 06:59.201
that you should be talking

06:59.331 --> 07:01.508
about the rest
of your fucking life.

07:01.638 --> 07:03.988
Look, if you really get kicked
out, you can move in with me,

07:04.119 --> 07:06.861
but marriage,
it's a big deal, all right?

07:06.991 --> 07:08.950
Needs to be taken seriously.

07:09.080 --> 07:11.213
Plus, you know,
there's the band to consider.

07:11.343 --> 07:12.867
- Pags, I already told you,
dude,

07:12.997 --> 07:15.043
I'm not coming at
this lightly.

07:15.173 --> 07:18.089
And besides, maybe my mom
kicking me out is a sign

07:18.220 --> 07:19.787
that now is the time
for me to do it.

07:19.917 --> 07:21.092
- You know what, my man?

07:21.223 --> 07:23.747
If that's the way you feel
about it, sláinte.

07:23.878 --> 07:24.705
- See?
That's my boy.

07:24.835 --> 07:26.837
- Great.

07:26.968 --> 07:29.753
So you're going away in a week.
Now he's getting married.

07:29.884 --> 07:31.276
Wanna tell me who I'm supposed
to hang out with.

07:31.407 --> 07:34.236
- All right.
Cue music.

07:34.366 --> 07:38.632
I want high energy,
clean lines.

07:38.762 --> 07:40.851
Remember your spacing for me.

07:40.982 --> 07:42.723
